This paper deals with the stability of Kalman filtering, which is a topic in control theory and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of linear matrix inequalities (LMI), which is a common tool in optimization and information theory, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper presents numerical examples, indicating that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper involves the use of Markov chains, which is a topic in probability theory and stochastic processes, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MA (Machine Learning).
